        "description": "Pulsar Arena is a rhythm-based shooter controlled entirely with head-tracking that takes aspects from tug-of-war and hot-potato and wraps them up in a musical adventure in space. \n\nThe arena pits two combatants in a large hourglass, balanced between a beating binary pulsar system with a 360-degree playing field. Looking at a PolyBlock on the beat will target and shoot it. Mix up gameplay by using combos on special effect PolyBlocks to get Electric and Bomb balls.\n\nEvery PolyBlock that you destroy is sent up the hourglass-shaped arena to your opponent. Surrounding you is a floor split into four rings keeping you safe from the Pulsar star below you. Too many PolyBlocks will degrade your floor. Avoid decimation and keep destroying those PolyBlocks!\n\nThe tournament of the future brings the best of music, VR, and a full 360 playing field.\n\nFrom the team that brought you Proton Pulse and Vanguard V.\n\nCreative Director:  Justin Moravetz",
